The paper is about query performance prediction in database management systems, which is a core topic in the field of database systems (cs.DB). The paper proposes a novel neural network architecture for this task, which involves deep learning techniques (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses optimizations to reduce training overhead, which is related to distributed computing (cs.DC). Finally, the paper uses neural networks to predict query latency, which is a common application of neural networks (cs.NE).
